#1 <s>As an introverted creative working independently and placing great value on privacy, it shouldn't be a contradiction, but it often is. Most online sources and coaches advise working with (evil) tech giants and being extroverted. Pitch here, follow the algorithm, show your personality. Get a blue tick on that service, be available 24/7, answer inquiries with a video of yourself, respond immediately. Video, video, video.
#2 <s>1/3
#3 <s>For me, this is a year of changes.
#4 <s>I don't want to feed the tech giants with money, data, and my energy. Or coaches who have their own extroverted solution and try to sell it to everyone. I'm looking for new ways to run my business and fighting against my long-held belief that one has to do something a certain way to succeed.
#5 <s>Wish me luck!
The first steps I have already taken.
I cancelled my Facebook account, removed all Meta and Pinterest trackers from my website, and deleted my private WhatsApp account.
Yesterday, I also removed Google Analytics, the last external tracker from my website, and feel good about it.
Recently, I subscribed to a European CRM to have better DSGVO support, and will move my business there in the coming weeks.
I transferred my MX account to Proton and now have full SPF, DKIM, and DMARC without having to pay anything to Google for normal email validation.
3/3
