@user4 @user3 You can do it! And I will gladly help you with my experiences.
Website: Check out @user5. This seems simple, looks good, and is open-source. I will switch one of my websites to this before the next renewal.
Signal: Check out cal.com. This is an open-source calendar service with integrations that allow you to schedule video calls with Element Call, Jitsi, etc. Signal is also supported, but I haven't tested whether it's for messages or videos yet.
I can recommend @user6. End-to-end encryption, decentralized, open-source.
